  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Framework Agreement with The Norwegian Center for Holocaust and Minority Studies on religious and ethnic minorities in conflict-affected areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Framework Agreement 2020-22 with The Norwegian Center for Holocaust and Minority Studies (HL-senteret) on religious and ethnic minorities in conflict-affected areas.The overall objective of the programme is to improve the situation for religious and ethnic minorities in conflict-affected areas, especially in South-East Asia and Middle East / North Africa with a special focus on Myanmar and Iraq. Expected results include increased knowledge on genocide prevention, with lessons learned from country cases.The project&#x2019;s target groups are civil society organizations and academics in these countries, who work to strengthen minority rights. The project aims to improve the competence, network and resources of these groups. Core topics include mass atrocity prevention and inclusive citizenship,</narrative>
  </description>
